# Application SSO Lab (Entra ID)

## Overview
This project demonstrates how Single Sign-On (SSO) is implemented using Microsoft Entra ID. Single sign-on (SSO) adds security and convenience when users sign on to applications in Microsoft Entra ID by enabling a user in organization to sign in to every application they use with only one account. Once the user logs into an application, that credential is used for all the other applications they need access to.

## Steps Implemented and Screenshots:

- Created enterprise application

- Assigned users/groups
- Configured Single Sign-On (SAML)



## Key Concepts
- Single Sign-On (SSO)
- Identity Provider (IdP)
- Service Provider (SP)
- Access Management

## Real-World Relevance
SSO enables secure and seamless access to applications, reducing password fatigue and centralizing authentication.
